      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this heavy, drowning weight right now. It sounds like the pressure is crushing you, and that desire for everything to just stop is completely understandable when you're carrying so much. Please know that you don't have to face this alone, and there are people who can help you find a way out of this water.\n\nIf you are in immediate distress or feeling like you might hurt yourself, please reach out to a crisis line right away. In the US, you can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or text HOME to 741741 to connect with the Crisis Text Line. They are there to listen without judgment and help you find a path forward.\n\nEven though you feel like there is no way out, there is a way out, and it often starts with taking just one small step, like talking to someone who cares. You are not defined by these exams or your parents' expectations; you are a person who deserves support and rest.\n\n*   **988 Suicide & Crisis Lifeline**: Call or text 988 (US)\n*   **Crisis Text Line**: Text HOME to 741",
